[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ben Wilson: Cardiff keeper joins AFC Wimbledon on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League Two side AFC Wimbledon have signed Cardiff City goalkeeper Ben Wilson on a 28-day loan deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 23-year-old has made one senior appearance for the Bluebirds, which came against the Dons in the League Cup earlier this season.
Wilson has obtained international clearance and is eligible to make his debut for Wimbledon in Tuesday's game at Accrington Stanley.
The Dons' number one James Shea has been suffering with a groin injury.
